Articles.Content:
64bit KSP keeps crashing after a couple of minutes, modding makes it even worse. Is this a known problem?

It's not running out of memory, only 2GB when crash happens, no particular action seems to trigger it. Went back to unmodded install, seems to hold up for 15 minutes then crashes.

Only have Terrain Scatters and Terrain Detail on high, no other options changed. No crash logs either.

 

Yeah no matter what it keeps crashing after a couple minutes, quite literally unplayable. Has been like that the whole pre-release as well.

Edited April 20, 2016 by TampaPowers

I've been having the same problem.

I just bought the game today, played about 2 hours, and now it crashes about every 10 minutes.

I reported this on Steam and someone suggested that it could be a memory leak. I don't know where it would be leaking to or from. It's dry around my computer, so that can't be it. I have 16 gigs of ram and no mods.

I'm just starting the game today on career mode, so I don't even have in game assets.

I've been having this issue too, it seems to happen the most when clicking stuff in the VAB/SPH.

I would post the crash logs but they don't have any useful information in 'em It just...stops.
Come to think of it, yeah mostly VAB/SPH where it crashes, once while I was on the Mun though, but with crash report that time.

I am also having constant crashes.

Damn, I was in the middle of building a reusable rocket based on the Energia II.

Every time the game runs it writes a log file called output_log.txt into the KSP_Data (for 32bit) or KSP_x64_Data (for 64bit) folder.  This is the most important log file for diagnosing what is going wrong.  You should upload the file to a file sharing service and post a link here.  You should also include a DxDiag report (there are instructions for generating this in one of the sticky threads in this sub-forum).

I notice after the crash...If I ask Steam to verify the files. It always finds 1 or 2 that are missing and need to be acquired.

I hope it all gets sorted out soon. What little time I've had in game seemed to be really fun, and I can see myself sinking several hours into it.

Right now I don't even want to start it up knowing the the inevitable crash is coming.

Also from SunBurstMoon:

 

Quote

Easy steps to reproduce 100% of the time:
1. Start any game (can be new career or sandbox with default settings)
Go in VAB or SPH and add any part that allow surface attachment, like a command pod
2. Switch symmetry to 2 anything other than 1 (off)
3. Then pick but do not place any part that can be surface attached AND will add staging
